
Development Guide
This section documents the technical structure, navigation architecture, HTML template, and wireframe for the Supercars website.

Site Directory Structure
The following directory structure organizes all assets for the Supercars site. Files are separated by type into dedicated subfolders for maintainability.

Path
Contents / Purpose
supercars/
Root directory contains all HTML files and subdirectories
  images/
All JPG/PNG/WebP image files (car photos, logos, hero backgrounds)
  styles/
CSS stylesheets styles.css (main), responsive.css (breakpoints)
  fonts/
Any locally hosted font files (fallback for Bebas Neue, Inter)
  trinity/
Holy Trinity deep-dive pages p1.html, laferrari.html, 918.html
  brands/
Individual brand pages ferrari.html, lamborghini.html, mclaren.html, etc.
  culture/
Car culture sub-pages (films, games, motorsport)
  index.html
Home page hero, brands overview, Holy Trinity cards, sidebar
  brands.html
Full brands hub page organized by national car culture
  culture.html
Car culture in film, games, and motorsport
  hobbies.html
Hot Wheels collecting, LEGO Technic builds, sim racing
  trinity.html
Holy Trinity hub links to all three individual car deep-dives


