HTML Template
The template below serves as the master structure for all pages on the site. Each section is self-documented with comments explaining its role. All pages are generated from this single template.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Supercars [Page Title]</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles/styles.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <!-- IDENTITY BLOCK: logo + brand name, appears on every page -->
  <header class="site-header" role="banner">
    <div class="header-inner">
      <div class="site-identity">
        <span class="site-logo-icon" aria-hidden="true">🏎️</span>
        <span class="site-logo-text">Supercars</span>
      </div>
      <!-- NAVIGATION: sticky, links to all main sections -->
      <nav aria-label="Main Navigation">
        <ul>
          <li><a href="../index.html">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="../brands.html">Brands</a></li>
          <li><a href="../culture.html">Culture</a></li>
          <li><a href="../hobbies.html">Hobbies</a></li>
          <li><a href="../trinity.html">Holy Trinity</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT: primary page content goes here -->
  <main id="main-content">
    <section aria-labelledby="page-heading">
      <h1 id="page-heading">[Page Heading]</h1>
      <p>[Page intro text]</p>
      <!-- Page-specific content blocks -->
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- FOOTER: copyright, links, tagline -->
  <footer class="site-footer" role="contentinfo">
    <div class="footer-inner">
      <span class="footer-logo">🏎️ Supercars</span>
      <nav class="footer-nav" aria-label="Footer Navigation">
        <a href="../index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="../brands.html">Brands</a>
        <a href="../trinity.html">Holy Trinity</a>
      </nav>
      <p class="footer-copy">&copy; 2025 Vaishvik Dogiparthi</p>
    </div>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>

Wireframe
The wireframe consists of one plain HTML file per navigation section. Pages are unstyled (black and white, default browser fonts) but fully linked together. Each page states its section name and lists the content topics it will contain when complete.

File
Heading Text
Topics Listed on Page
index.html
Supercars Home
Hero banner, brand links, Holy Trinity cards, culture sidebar, hobbies
brands.html
Supercar Brands
Italian culture (Ferrari, Lamborghini, Pagani), British (McLaren), Swedish (Koenigsegg), French (Bugatti)
trinity.html
The Holy Trinity
McLaren P1, Ferrari LaFerrari, Porsche 918 Spyder specs, history, significance
culture.html
Car Culture
Films (Fast & Furious, Rush, Cars), TV (Formula 1), Games (NFS, Gran Turismo)
hobbies.html
Supercar Hobbies
Hot Wheels die-cast collecting, LEGO Technic car sets, sim racing


GitHub repository name: vaishvik-supercars  |  All wireframe pages link to each other via a plain <nav> block at the top.

Interactivity List (Bonus)

Interactive Element
Type
Purpose & Notes
Holy Trinity hover cards
CSS + JS event
On hover, dim the car image and reveal name + specs overlay. Keyboard-accessible via :focus-visible.
Favorite Car field
contenteditable
Visitors type their favorite car directly on the page no form submission needed. Simple entry point.
Hamburger nav menu
CSS checkbox trick
Mobile navigation toggle using a hidden checkbox input no JS required, accessible via label.
Brand spec comparison
JS table filter
Future: allow visitors to select two brands/cars and compare specs side-by-side in a dynamic table.
0–60 mph timer widget
JS countdown
Future: animated timer that counts down from 0 to the car's 0–60 mph time for each Trinity card.



SECTION 2
Design Guide
This section documents the visual design decisions for the Supercars site, including layout, color palette, typography, style rules, and media assets.

Layout & Storyboard
The site uses a two-column CSS grid layout on desktop (2/3 main content + 1/3 sidebar), collapsing to a single column on screens below 900px. The layout follows the rule of thirds: the hero occupies the top visual third, the content grid fills the middle, and the footer anchors the bottom.

[ STICKY HEADER Logo   |   Brands   Culture   Hobbies   Holy Trinity ]
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[ HERO Full-width   "Speed. Power. Beauty." tagline + H1 ]
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[ CONTENT GRID  ───────────────────────────────  |  SIDEBAR ─── ]
[ 2/3 Brands, Holy Trinity cards, spec tables ]  |  [ 1/3 Car Culture, Hobbies, Fav Car ]
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[ FOOTER Logo + tagline   |   Nav links   |   Copyright ]


Color Palette
The palette is built around a dark background with a racing red accent. Near-white body text ensures high contrast. Muted grays serve as secondary text and UI dividers.

Chip
Name
Hex
Usage
 
Racing Red
#E10600
Primary accent nav underlines, headings, borders, logo text, footer bar
 
Red Bright
#FF3322
Hover states brand card border, nav link hover, interactive highlights
 
Midnight Black
#0A0A0A
Page background creates the high-contrast, high-performance atmosphere
 
Carbon Dark
#141414
Card backgrounds Trinity cards, brand list items, interactive elements
 
Asphalt
#111111
Header and footer background slightly lighter than page BG for depth
 
Near White
#F0F0F0
Primary body text WCAG-level contrast against dark backgrounds
 
Dim Gray
#AAAAAA
Secondary text subtitles, nav link default state, intro paragraphs
 
Muted Gray
#888888
Footer text, metadata, captions, least-important UI labels
 
Dark Border
#2A2A2A
Card borders, list dividers, UI separators subtle structure without brightness


Style Guide
The following style rules define the visual presentation of the site's key elements. Full CSS is in styles/styles.css; this guide lists anticipated rules organized by component.

Typography
Element
Font / Size
Notes
Logo / Display headings
Bebas Neue, fallback Impact
All-caps, 1.7rem (header), 5.5rem (hero), 1.6rem (section h2)
Body text
Inter 400, 1rem / 1.7 line-height
Default text color #F0F0F0 on #0A0A0A background
Nav links
Inter 700, 0.85rem
Uppercase, letter-spacing 0.07em, color #AAA default → #FFF hover → #E10600 active
Section headings (h2)
Bebas Neue, 1.6rem
Color #E10600, border-bottom 1px rgba(225,6,0,0.3), uppercase
Card overlay text
Bebas Neue 1.1rem / Inter 0.75rem
Car name in Bebas Neue white; stats in Inter semi-transparent white
Footer / metadata
Inter 400, 0.75–0.8rem
Color #888, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.1em


Layout & Spacing
Max content width: 1100px, centered with auto margins
Gutter / padding: 1.5rem on mobile; scales up with clamp()
Content grid: grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr (desktop) → 1fr (≤900px)
Sidebar: position: sticky, top: 60px + 1.5rem (below header)
Hero padding: clamp(3rem, 10vw, 6rem) top and bottom

Header & Navigation
Header: position: sticky, top: 0, z-index: 100, background #111, border-bottom 3px solid #E10600
Nav links: underline animation via ::after pseudo-element, left/right transition from center
Active link: color #E10600, underline visible at rest
Mobile (≤768px): hamburger toggle appears, nav collapses to vertical list

Cards (Holy Trinity)
Aspect ratio: 4/3, overflow: hidden, border-radius: 6px
Hover: image scale(1.06) + brightness(0.4), overlay opacity 0 → 1
Focus: box-shadow 0 0 0 3px #E10600 for keyboard accessibility

Sidebar Sections
Background: #141414, border: 1px solid #2A2A2A, border-left: 3px solid #E10600
Sticky below header, drops to static on mobile (≤900px)
Culture list items separated by 1px border-bottom #2A2A2A
contenteditable field: dashed red border, turns solid on :focus

